        "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>I use the text area to reveal how many objects I have created from a specific class<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Don't use a JTextArea.<\/p>\n\n<p>Instead I would suggest you should be using a <code>JList<\/code>. Read the section from the Swing tutorial on <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/list.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">How to Use Lists<\/a> for more information and examples.<\/p>\n\n<p>The <code>JList<\/code> has a <code>locationToIndex(...)<\/code> method which will give you the row where the mouse was clicked. Then you can get the object from the list.<\/p>\n",
